TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {4808=* Won their first and only divisional title in 1991 after luring Wayne Gretzky to California. Two years later, they won their first conference championship but lost to the Montreal Canadiens in the Stanley Cup Final., 4050=* They advanced to the Stanley Cup Final for the second time and will play the New Jersey Devils in the best-of-seven series starting May 30 in Newark, New Jersey., 4574=* During the 2011-12 regular season, the Kings (40-27-15) finished third in their division and scraped into the playoffs as the eighth-ranked team in the Western Conference., 3869=* The Kings head coach is Canadian Darryl Sutter, a former NHL forward with the Chicago Blackhawks. As a coach, he has been in charge of Chicago, San Jose and the Calgary Flames. He took the Flames to the Stanley Cup in 2004, losing to Tampa Bay. This is his first season with the Kings., 5740=Mon, 28 May 22:48:00 2012, 3564=* The captain is American right wing Dustin Brown, who has been with the Kings since he was selected by them in the 2003 draft. Brown represented the United States at the 2010 Winter Olympics, winning a silver medal., 5262=* The Kings were founded in 1967 as part of the NHL's first major expansion that added six new franchises and doubled the size of the league. The other new franchises were the California Seals, Minnesota North Stars, Philadelphia Flyers, Pittsburgh Penguins and St Louis Blues.}
